channel.description:
I was spawning jads everywhere in the wildy, and made him drop firecapes. So i tested him out, And i killed him in 1 hit!!! He had no hp, so i hit a 0, and he just died!! I changed everything in the npc.cfg file, i made jad have 314 hp and i saved it. But there was no diffrence?
ROFLMAO PLEASE SOMEONE HELP!!

item.title: Ffs! i really need help here!@@@@@@@
item.dc:creator: @Crappyservermaker Crappyservermaker
item.description:
@Crappyservermaker wrote:

[quote=“juggalofamilyinc, post:24, topic:17562”]Alright, I had a noob bother me for hours on msn about this same thing …

are you doing ::npc ### and spawning him, and killing him? because if so he will never have hp … this is not adding a monster to the game. You need to open up your autospawn.cfg and make a new line like

spawn = #### coordx coordy height rangex+ rangey+ rangex-

(on the same line)
rangey- walktype description

then he will spawn there forever, and you can fight him …[/quote]

ANd how the fuck are we supposed to know:

spawn = #### coordx coordy height rangex+ rangey+ rangex-

(on the same line)
rangey- walktype description

And all that shit?! (Except for coords and id)
